---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout 
  title="Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy - Track Your Labs"
  description="How Track Your Labs protects your consumer health data under state privacy laws."
>
  <main class="flex-1 px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-10 pb-6 md:pb-8 lg:pb-10 pt-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full">
    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-full break-words">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="text-sm mb-2"><strong>Last updated:</strong> August 12, 2025</p>
      <p class="text-sm mb-2"><strong>Company:</strong> Snowflake Health, LLC ("Snowflake Health," "we," "us," or "our")</p>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6"><strong>Service:</strong> Track Your Labs – <a href="https://www.trackyourlabs.com/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">https://www.trackyourlabs.com/</a></p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">TL;DR — Quick Summary</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Anonymous tool = zero CHD collected or stored.</strong></li>
        <li><strong>HIPAA-grade security</strong> protects processing, though no data is permanently kept.</li>
        <li>Waitlist is strictly for feature updates—completely disconnected from CHD.</li>
        <li>You control your waitlist data; you can delete it anytime.</li>
        <li>Expect advance notice for any policy changes.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <p class="break-words">
        This policy explains how we handle <strong>Consumer Health Data (CHD)</strong>—personal health-related information tied to identity—under U.S. state laws like Washington's <em>My Health My Data Act</em>, Nevada's SB 370, and similar regulations. This policy supplements our main Privacy Policy and applies where it provides stronger protection.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. What Is Consumer Health Data (CHD)?</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        CHD means any <em>personally identifiable</em> health information, including medical conditions, diagnoses, treatments, or bodily functions, as defined by applicable state consumer health laws.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. What CHD We Collect</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Anonymous tool usage:</strong> We collect <strong>none</strong>. When you use the Track Your Labs anonymous lab result viewer:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
            <li>No personal information is required.</li>
            <li>No CHD is collected, stored, or linked to you.</li>
            <li>Once the session ends (e.g., by closing your browser tab), <strong>all data is automatically discarded</strong>. Privacy by design.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. Optional Waitlist Participation</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li>If you choose to join our <strong>waitlist</strong>, you may share your email (and optionally name).</li>
        <li>This information is used <strong>only</strong> to notify you when account-based features become available.</li>
        <li>Waitlist info is kept entirely separate from any lab data and is <strong>never</strong> used for CHD or other privacy-sensitive purposes.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. Data Handling & Security</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>HIPAA-compliant infrastructure</strong> is used to process anonymous uploads securely and protect against unauthorized access.</li>
        <li>Since <strong>no CHD is collected or stored</strong>, there is no data to delete or retain.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Your Rights Concerning CHD</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Anonymous tool use:</strong> No data exists—there is nothing to access, correct, or delete.</li>
        <li><strong>Waitlist data:</strong> You can request deletion of your contact information anytime by emailing <strong>privacy@trackyourlabs.com</strong>. We'll confirm once it's removed.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class="break-words">If this CHD Policy changes materially, we will inform you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Email</strong>, if you're on the waitlist; or</li>
        <li><strong>On-site notice</strong>, if you visit the site.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We will provide at least <strong>30 days' notice</strong> before changes take effect—per legal requirements.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Contact Information</h2>
      <p class="break-words">For any questions or requests, reach us at:</p>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words"><strong>Snowflake Health, LLC</strong></p>
      <p class="break-words">Email: <strong>privacy@trackyourlabs.com</strong></p>
      <p class="break-words">Website: <a href="https://www.trackyourlabs.com/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">https://www.trackyourlabs.com/</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }
  
  .prose table {
    width: 100%;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>